nodes.bodyText: I think there might be a very slight chance the processing thread moved onto another transform when the LogHandler haven't done transforming the log entries in previous one. But I think the it should be very rare(log transform should be almost instant) and I would argue that it's probably better to keep the logging just best effort instead of introducing locks to guarantee 100% metadata correctness?
